<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words Only in TWL — Valid in North America But Not SOWPODS</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">While SOWPODS is designed as a superset containing almost all TWL words, a small number of entries — roughly 600-800 — exist only in TWL. These are typically very recent additions that NASPA approved before the international committee incorporated them, or Americanisms the international body hasn't accepted.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">TWL vs SOWPODS Overview</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">~187K</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL total words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">~280K</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SOWPODS total words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">~700</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL-exclusive words</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why TWL-Only Words Exist</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/10">
    <p class="text-blue-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">⏰ Timing Gaps</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">NASPA releases updates on a different schedule than WESPA. New TWL additions may take 1-3 years to appear in SOWPODS.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">🇺🇸 Americanisms</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Some American slang and cultural terms are accepted by NASPA but rejected by the international committee as too regional.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
    <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">📋 Different Criteria</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">NASPA and WESPA use different linguistic standards for what constitutes a "valid English word" — leading to occasional disagreements.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
    <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">🔄 Recent Additions</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Words added in TWL's latest update (2023) may not appear in SOWPODS until its next revision cycle.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy for Dictionary Awareness</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Always verify before playing:</span> If you're switching between online platforms (some use TWL, some use SOWPODS), a word you used last game may not be valid this game. Our finder shows both dictionaries.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">TWL-exclusive words are rare:</span> Unlike the ~40,000 SOWPODS exclusives, TWL-only words number under 1,000. Focus your study time on SOWPODS exclusives if you play both formats.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Challenge wisely:</span> If an opponent plays a word you don't recognise, consider whether you're playing TWL or SOWPODS before challenging. A SOWPODS-valid word challenged in a SOWPODS game costs YOU points.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Dictionary Comparison Cheat Sheet</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">✓ TWL Advantages</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Smaller dictionary means fewer obscure words to memorise. Focused on North American English. Used in NASPA tournaments, most US clubs, and many online platforms by default.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/10">
    <p class="text-blue-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">✓ SOWPODS Advantages</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">93,000 more words = more scoring options. Used internationally (WESPA). More loanwords, slang, and archaic terms accepted. QI alone changes Q-tile strategy entirely.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The TWL-only list is <span class="text-white font-medium">tiny compared to SOWPODS exclusives</span>. If you learn SOWPODS, you automatically know 99.6% of TWL. The reverse isn't true — TWL players miss ~40,000 valid international words.</p>
</div>

